Archiving utility similar to tar but producing more compact
archives that can then be easily read with DataInputStream.

To invoke arh utility from the command line use command

    java -jar arh.jar  <command> <arh-file> [files...]

Further the part "java -jar arh.jar" is simply referred as "arh".

Commands:

arh  c  <archive>  <files>...
  Create archive containing specified files. Directories are added recursively.

arh  t  <archive>
  List names of all files contained in this archive.

arh  x  <archive>
  Extract all files from the archive in the current directory.

arh  v
  Print program version and exit.

arh  h
  Print short help message and exit.
